ily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":6,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":15,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Roger de Macclesfield was born in 1209, in Macclesfield, Cheshire, England, his father, Earl Gilbert de Macclesfield, was 20 and his mother, Countess Isabel de Macclesfield, was 30. He had at least 3 sons with Isabel de Orreby. He died in 1246, in his hometown, at the age of 37."},"et":{"1209–1246":"1209–1246","1216–1295":"1216–1295","1235–1310":"1235–1310","1237–Male":"1237–Surnud","1239–1308":"1239–1308","1189–Male":"1189–Surnud","1180–Female":"1180–Surnud","abt. 1239":"umbes 1239","abt. 1237":"umbes 1237","1295":"1295","1180":"1180","1239":"1239","1216":"1216","1215":"1215","1237":"1237","1235":"1235","1246":"1246","1224":"1224","1189":"1189","1310":"1310","1209":"1209","1308":"1308","Macclesfield, Cheshire, Eng.":"Macclesfield, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Macclesfield, Cheshire, England":"Macclesfield, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"1209–12